                    <span>...and the ideas in it changed the way I write.
<br />
<br />Now, I haven't read _all_ writing books, obviously, but usually I get to the end and have learned nothing new.  If you decide to review Card's book, and consider it basic:  identify the books you found more helpful!
<br />
<br />As for me, I found new detail on:  POV; brainstorming for ideas; the types of stories and where they should start; how to put info in as part of the narrative, without the "info dump" that stops the story; and how to make characters interesting with multiple motivations.</span>
                  
                    <div class="CustomerReviewSummary">Creating Characters For Your Worlds</div>
                    <div>
                      <span class="ItemCaption">Rating: </span>
